User Setup

Before anyone can use your computer, they must have an account on your
system. Use the User Setup window to to assign (and remove) user
accounts and to change the permissions assigned to those accounts,
thereby controlling the types of tasks a user can perform.

The User Setup window also lets you change the properties of accounts
(whether or not the account has permission to modify or shutdown the
system or whether or not someone is a Desktop user) and enables you to
manage \d(groups^group) to which users belong. You must have owner permissions
to add, delete, and change user accounts and group accounts, and to
change user permissions.

The following windows are provided for User Setup:

        \k(User Setup Window)
        \k(User Setup: Account Permissions Window)
        \k(User Setup: User Account Properties Window)
        \k(User Setup: Group Properties Window)
^1^User Setup Window
^$20
\k{User Setup}
1. User Setup Window

Use the User Setup Window to display an icon for each user allowed to
log in to your system. This window lets you add, delete, and change
properties and permissions of user accounts. You also can maintain the
\d(groups^group) and reserved accounts (accounts with a User ID - UID - from 0
to 99) defined for your system.

The buttons available from the User Setup window are:

        \k(Actions Button^^Actions ButtonUS)
        \k(View Button^^View ButtonUS)
        \k(Account Button^^Account ButtonUS)
        \k(Help Button^^Help ButtonUS)
^2^Actions Button=Actions ButtonUS
^$30
1. \k{User Setup Window}
   1.1 Actions Button

The Actions button lets you set the permissions for user and
reserved accounts, depending upon what was selected with the \k(View button^^View ButtonUS).
The Actions button also lets you exit the User Setup window.

Clicking on the Actions button displays a menu with the following
options:

        \k(Permissions)
        \k(Exit)
^3^Permissions
^$40
1. \k{User Setup Window}
   1.1 \k{Actions Button^^Actions ButtonUS}
       1.1.1 Permissions

The Permissions menu option lets the owner account change user and
reserved account permissions. This option is only active when either
user or reserved accounts are displayed in the User Setup window.

Selecting the Permissions menu option displays the User Setup:
Account Permissions window.

More information: \k(User Setup: Account Permissions Window)
^3^Exit
^$50
1. \k{User Setup Window}
   1.1 \k{Actions Button^^Actions ButtonUS}
       1.1.2 Exit

The Exit menu option lets you exit from the User Setup window.
