1. \k{User Setup Window}
   1.3 Account Button

The Account button lets you add and delete user, group, and reserved
accounts. You also can modify properties for the accounts defined on
your system.

Clicking on the Account button displays a menu with the following
options:

        \k(New^^NewUS)
        \k(Delete^^DeleteUS)
        \k(Properties^^PropertiesUS)
^3^New=NewUS
^$110
1. \k{User Setup Window}
   1.3 \k{Account Button^^Account ButtonUS}
       1.3.1 New

The New menu option lets you add new user accounts, reserved accounts, and
groups to your system.

The window that appears when you click on the New menu option depends
on which icons were selected with the View button:

   o Users View: User Setup: Add New User Account

   o Groups View: User Setup: Add New Group

   o Reserved View: User Setup: Add New Reserved Account

The User Setup: Add New User Account window and the User Setup: Add
New Reserved Account window request the same information as the User
Setup: User Account Properties window. The User Setup: Add New Group
window requests the same information as the User Setup: Group Proper-
ties window.

More information:

        \k(User Setup: User Account Properties Window)
        \k(User Setup: Group Properties Window)
^3^Delete=DeleteUS
^$120
1. \k{User Setup Window}
   1.3 \k{Account Button^^Account ButtonUS}
       1.3.2 Delete

The Delete menu option lets you delete user and reserved accounts and
groups from your system. When you delete a user account, that user can
no longer log into your system. Clicking on the Delete menu option
displays the User Setup: Confirmation window. The User Setup:
Confirmation window contains two options:

   o The Remove User's Files option confirms that you want to remove
     the user's files. This option is selected when the window
     appears, indicating that the user's files are removed when the
     user is removed.

     Note: If the Backup User's Files option is selected, a
     confirmation notice appears before the user's files are removed.
     The notice enables you to change you mind about deleting the
     user's files.

   o The Backup User's Files options enables you to backup the user's
     files before they are removed. If you want to backup the user's
     files, click on the box on this line.

The User Setup: Confirmation window has three buttons:

   o Yes Button: This button begins the action of removing the user
     and the user's files. If the Backup User's Files options is
     selected, a window appears prompting you to insert a floppy disk
     for backing up the user's files.

   o No Button: This button closes the User Setup: Confirmation window
     without deleting the user.

   o Help Button: This button provides on-line help for the User
     Setup: Confirmation window.

Caution: You should not delete reserved accounts or pre-existing
groups. Deleting a reserved account could prohibit you from performing
certain tasks on your system. Deleting pre-existing groups could cause
permission problems when some users attempt to read or access certain
files.
