1. \k{User Setup Window}
   1.3 \k{Account Button^^Account ButtonUS}
       1.3.3 Properties

The Properties menu option lets you change the information associated
with users and groups.

For user and reserved accounts, you can change the name, comment,
group, home directory, shell, user ID, whether the account is a Desktop
or Nondesktop account, and the style of the Desktop (OPEN LOOK or Motif).
For groups, you can change the group name and group ID number.

Selecting the Properties menu option displays either the User Setup:
User Account Properties or User Setup: User Account Properties window,
which are identical if user or reserved account icons are displayed,
or the User Setup: Group Properties window if group icons are
displayed.

More information:

        \k(User Setup: User Account Properties Window)
        \k(User Setup: Group Properties Window)
