2. User Setup: Account Permissions Window

Use the User Setup: Account Permissions window to change the permis-
sions for a user account. A user's permissions determine what that
user can do on your system. For example, to change permissions for a
user, you must be designated as the owner of the system.

The User Setup: Account Permissions window displays a list of account
permissions, each with check box. If you click on the first check box
(Selected User is the System Owner), all other check boxes are filled
in. This would give the selected user permissions to make any neces-
sary changes to the system.

To make a user the System Owner, you must have System Owner Account
permission. Initially, the account created during installation is the
System Owner. If you want to give another account System Owner Account
permissions, log in using the System Owner account and change the
permissions for the other account.

The following permission can be changed from this window:

   o Shutdown System 

   o Access Disks, Tapes, etc.

   o Access Remote Systems

   o Change Dialup Setup

   o Change Internet Setup

   o Administer Printers

   o Add/Remove Fonts

   o Add/Remove Applications

   o Advertise Local Folders/Files

   o Connect to Remote Folders/Files

Additional permissions may be available depending upon what additional
software is installed on your system.

The buttons available from the User Setup: Account Permissions window
are:

        \k(Apply Button^^Apply ButtonPERM)
        \k(Reset Button^^Reset ButtonPERM)
        \k(Cancel Button^^Cancel ButtonPERM)
        \k(Help Button^^Help ButtonPERM)
^2^Apply Button=Apply ButtonPERM
^$190
2. \k{User Setup: Account Permissions Window}
   2.1 Apply Button

The Apply button immediately applies any changes made in the User
Setup: Account Permissions window, except that of removing Owner
designation from an account. This change does not take affect until
you exit from the User Setup window.

After applying the changes, the User Setup: Account Permissions window
closes.
^2^Reset Button=Reset ButtonPERM
^$200
2. \k{User Setup: Account Permissions Window}
   2.2 Reset Button

The Reset button reverses any changes you have not yet applied. The
User Setup: Account Permissions window remains open.
^2^Cancel Button=Cancel ButtonPERM
^$210
2. \k{User Setup: Account Permissions Window}
   2.3 Cancel Button

The Cancel button closes the User Setup: Account Permissions window
without saving any permission changes.
^2^Help Button=Help ButtonPERM
^$220
2. \k{User Setup: Account Permissions Window}
   2.4 Help Button

The Help button provides help for the User Setup: Account Permissions
window.
